<specimenCode id="DD626723FFFD270C67C9FEFD824791A5" box="[709,863,367,393]" collectionCode="ZFMK" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34613" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34613" name="Zoologisches Forschungsmuseum Alexander Koenig" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" type="Museum">ZFMK 67871</specimenCode>
(
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFFD270C6661FEFD82DA91A5" box="[877,962,367,393]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="TABLE 3. Codes, localities and co-ordinates for the types and taxa now regarded as junior synonyms of the Hyperolius species, used in figs. 4–10." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF">Table 3</tableCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFD270C66DBFEFC82FD91A4" bold="true" box="[983,997,366,392]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">“</emphasis>
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C66E9FEFD853A91A5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C66E9FEFD853A91A5" box="[997,1058,367,393]" country="Cameroon" county="Bakossi Mountains" latitude="4.95" longLatPrecision="1306" longitude="9.65" municipality="Edib Hills" name="From" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" stateProvince="South-West">From</location>
the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6D1F5522FFFD270C615DFEFD85DA91A5" box="[1105,1218,367,393]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Edib Hills</collectingMunicipality>
(ca. 
<elevation id="06E9286BFFFD270C61F4FEFD80349182" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" unit="m" value="1200.0">
<quantity id="4A3C62BDFFFD270C61F4FEFD844B91A5" box="[1272,1363,367,393]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" unit="m" value="1200.0">1,200 m</quantity>
above sea level
</elevation>
), 
<collectingCounty id="641AB7D4FFFD270C644CFE0183039181" box="[320,539,403,429]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Bakossi Mountains</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4F0001BAFFFD270C672AFE0183B09181" box="[550,680,403,429]" country="Cameroon" name="South-West" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">South-West</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFD270C67BCFE01823D9181" box="[688,805,403,429]" name="Cameroon" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFFD270C6638FE01828E9181" box="[820,918,403,431]" degrees="4" direction="north" minutes="57" orientation="latitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" precision="925" value="4.95">4° 57′ N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFFD270C66AEFE0185199181" box="[930,1025,403,431]" degrees="9" direction="east" minutes="39" orientation="longitude" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" precision="925" value="9.65">9° 39′ E</geoCoordinate>
).” 
<collectorName id="2031AA8EFFFD270C612DFE0185779181" box="[1057,1135,403,429]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Colour</collectorName>
in life, phase J: back olive to translucent dark green extending to limbs, with a pale green hourglass pattern. 
<collectorName id="2031AA8EFFFD270C6157FE2585AF91FD" box="[1115,1207,439,465]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Phase F</collectorName>
: back dark brown to black with greenish spots and bright red areas on upper legs, feet and hands. 
<collectorName id="2031AA8EFFFD270C6121FE49854191D9" box="[1069,1113,475,501]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">The</collectorName>
dorsal surface has a goldenyellow dense marbling. 
<collectorName id="2031AA8EFFFD270C64D8FE6D83189235" box="[468,512,511,537]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">The</collectorName>
females may be brown with reddish speckles (
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFD270C6107FE6D85CC9236" author="Portik, D. M. &amp; Jongsma, G. F. M. &amp; Kouete, M. T. &amp; Scheinberg, L. A. &amp; Freiermuth, B. &amp; Tapondjou, W. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C." box="[1035,1236,511,538]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" pagination="37 - 67" refId="ref33245" refString="Portik, D. M., Jongsma, G. F. M., Kouete, M. T., Scheinberg, L. A., Freiermuth, B., Tapondjou, W. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. (2016) A survey of amphibians and reptiles in the foothills of Mount Kupe, Cameroon. Amphibian &amp; Reptile Conservation, 10 [Special Section], e 131, 37 - 67." type="journal article" year="2016">
<collectorName id="2031AA8EFFFD270C6107FE6D85499235" box="[1035,1105,511,537]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Portik</collectorName>
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFD270C6154FE6D85929235" box="[1112,1162,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFD270C659BFDD585449285" blockId="42.[151,1437,583,825]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
Sequences were available from 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C64FBFDD5839D924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C64FBFDD5839D924D" box="[503,645,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="Edib Village" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Edib Village</location>
, the 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFFD270C67BBFDD583FF924D" box="[695,743,583,609]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C6640FDD58280924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C6640FDD58280924D" box="[844,920,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="Manjo" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Manjo</location>
, 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C66AEFDD5851F924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C66AEFDD5851F924D" box="[930,1031,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="Mt Kupe" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Mt Kupe</location>
, 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C611EFDD5856A924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C611EFDD5856A924D" box="[1042,1138,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="Mantem" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Mantem</location>
, 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C6170FDD585EC924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C6170FDD585EC924D" box="[1148,1268,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="Southwest" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Southwest</location>
, 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C61F2FDD5844D924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C61F2FDD5844D924D" box="[1278,1365,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="Littoral" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Littoral</location>
, 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C6052FDD58480924D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C6052FDD58480924D" box="[1374,1432,583,609]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="West" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">West</location>
, all in 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFD270C65DBFDF9805792A9" box="[215,335,619,645]" name="Cameroon" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
. 
<location id="881B9983FFFD270C6455FDF9809D92A9" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFFD270C659BFEB4834F9315:881B9983FFFD270C6455FDF9809D92A9" box="[345,389,619,645]" country="Cameroon" county="It" municipality="The" name="The" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">The</location>
minimum uncorrected 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFD270C6786FDF983B992A8" box="[650,673,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">p-</emphasis>
distances from other clades were 1.9–6.0% (
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFFD270C619DFDF985F092A9" box="[1169,1256,619,645]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="20.[151,239,762,788]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 2. Uncorrected minimum p-distances as percentages between the clades. GOE—Hyperolius goetzei, NOB—H. noblei, MAR—H. mariae, VIR—H. viridiflavus, GLA— H. glandicolor, MAG—H. marginatus, TUB—H. tuberculosa, BAN—H. bangwae, DIN—H. dintelmanni, MOR—H. marmoratus, NIT—H. nitidulus, SPA—H. spatzi, PAR—H. parallelus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370">Table 2</tableCitation>
). 
<collectingMunicipality id="6D1F5522FFFD270C61F0FDF9843092A9" box="[1276,1320,619,645]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">The</collectingMunicipality>
clade was identified following 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFFD270C6471FD1D83589285" author="Bell" box="[381,576,655,681]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" pagination="5223 - 5244" refId="ref28911" refString="Bell, R. C., Parra, J. L., Badjedjea, G., Barej, M. F., Blackburn, D. C., Burger, M., Channing, A., Dehling, J. M., Greenbaum, E., Gvozdik, V., Kielgast, J., Kusamba, C., Lotters, S., McLaughlin, P. J., Nagy, Z. T., Rodel, M. - O., Portik, D. M., Stuart, B. L., VanDerWal, J., Zassi-Boulou, A. G. &amp; Zamudio, K. R. (2017) Idiosyncratic responses to climate-driven forest fragmentation and marine incursions in reed frogs from Central Africa and the Gulf of Guinea Islands. Molecular Ecology, 26, 5223 - 5244. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / mec. 14260" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bell 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFD270C64BFFD1D80FC9285" box="[435,484,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<collectingCounty id="641AB7D4FFFD270C6747FD1D83449285" box="[587,604,655,681]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">It</collectingCounty>
is known from eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFD270C666FFD1D82C09285" box="[867,984,655,681]" name="Cameroon" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="15FFD3DDFFFD270C66EBFD1D85489285" box="[999,1104,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-63@40.[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 10. Localities of sequences (black circles), type localities (stars) and location of junior synonyms of Hyperolius noblei (A), H. goetzei (B), H. spatzi (C) and H. dintelmanni (D). Locality codes are explained in Table 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538300/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
