<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFFD270C65CBFD21834F9315" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFD270C65CBFD2180599339" blockId="42.[151,1437,583,825]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">
The most common pattern element in the description of the 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFFD270C6665FD21828192E1" box="[873,921,691,717]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFFD270C66B3FD21857092E1" authorityName="Lotters &amp; Schmitz" authorityYear="2004" box="[959,1128,691,717]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="42" pageNumber="343" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dintelmanni">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFFD270C66B3FD21857092E1" box="[959,1128,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">H. dintelmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dorsal marbling (100%), followed by green spots (50%) or a red speckle (50%). The percentages are not additive, as the pattern elements may be shared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFD270C65CBFC8D834F9315" blockId="42.[151,1437,583,825]" box="[199,599,799,825]" pageId="42" pageNumber="343">The advertisement call is unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
